The paper deals with distributed estimation in wireless sensor networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT), control systems (cs.SY), and machine learning (cs.MA) techniques. The problem of detecting and handling sensor defects is a key aspect of the paper, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the paper proposes a learning-based algorithm for distributed estimation, which is related to the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
